nd infrastructure setup for Sterling, based on customer\u2019s environment segregation requirement like separate environment for Test, development, and production environment. 8. Design and develop patterns based on customer requirement and use pattern engine based image deployment to deploy customers work load faster into the cloud environment. Also design the pattern for migrating the EDI interfaces to new Sterling platform. 9. Integrate the customer\u2019s Business process into the Cloud provisioning workflows. 10. Create the architecture for integration of AlinIQ with the help Bluemix cloud Solution. Design, Plan and Implement the Sterling solution with industry best standards in Error handling, automated monitoring, solve complex business problems with EDI solutions like multi-level SSCC (Serial Shipping Container Code), which will reduce time in handling of shipments in the supply chain process. 11. Implement the integration of Managed Security Services in Bluemix for AlinIQ, so the multiple end customers can be managed and supported from single portal. 12. Design and Develop secured solution for customers with Bluemix services in Cloud using AlinIQ Application. Transform the EDI platform to the Industry best standard solution using Sterling. 13. Design the eco system required to support the Bluemix and Sterling environments like Monitoring and event Management capability, Backup, Encryption of Data in Rest and Motion, Vulnerability scanning etc. 14. Work as the main technical interface to the clients on multiple tiers. 15. Participate in proof of concepts to assist in defining technology direction 16. Design and implement IBM Blockchain process on the critical business processes, based on the proof of concept that was delivered. 17. Work on the IBM MQ MFT migration to the latest architecture. Work on designing the MFT Automated monitoring tool, and configure the same for all the 550+ Abbott servers. 18. Work on Request for Proposal [RFP] response and Request 